This is a low budget movie with all of the expected problems with low budget films, but on the most part they did a very good job at telling a comedic fantasy adventure.

It's a really good story idea with lots of potential.  A pirate is sent 300 years in to his future to reclaim his treasure in modern day.  His treasure is unfortunately a demon summoning, world threatening amulet.  Sweet.  It also turns out that this pirate's treasure has more than one interesting relic.  Hollywood, get your hands on this script!

It went well until there was a detour to a cheesy house party.  Fine, but that part should have been prefaced with a good reason for going.  They already had the amulet.  Another bad decision was to have some of the actors wear wigs, when it would have brought more realism to the movie if they didn't wear them.

Otherwise, the movie is cute and the editing, sound, lighting and acting gets way better by the end.  .It feels like a small town production, which is inspiring to see.  We need more films like these.  And most of all we need to support them.
Great movie very tongue and cheek. The budget was low but quality was high.

Very Amusing.  Kudos for doing something creative and fun with little resources and time.  This is where good efforts come from, which may pay off later for the writers, film makers, actors and supporting staff.  You can either see things half full or half empty--I prefer half full and growing.  Keep it up!  Oh--this is also instructive if you want to understand how film-making and ambition germinate, stew start and progress to something more.  You can also identify what needs to be improved, but still enjoy it for what it is.  Kudos!
